headlines.description: — The Pistons' 28th loss in a row was unlike any of the many, many other defeats that came before it in what is now tied for the longest losing streak in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics send Detroit to NBA record-tying 28th straight loss, beating Pistons 128-122 in OT

headlines.description: — NBA assists leader Tyrese Haliburton had a career-high 20 without a turnover and scored 21 points to help the Indiana Pacers hold off the Chicago Bulls 120-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Haliburton has 20 assists in Pacers' 120-104 victory over Bulls

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored a season-high 44 points and Rudy Gobert had 20 points and 11 rebounds as the Minnesota Timberwolves held on for a 118-110 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores season-high 44, leads Timberwolves past Doncic-less Mavericks 118-110

events.name: Utah Jazz at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram and Trey Murphy III made clutch shots from outside, Larry Nance Jr. provided intensity in the paint and the Pelicans broke their habit of falling apart at the end of close games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Ingram, Trey Murphy III hit clutch baskets, Pelicans hold off Jazz 112-105

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic was perfect from the field and free throw line, finishing with 26 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists as the Denver Nuggets posted their highest point total of the season in a 142-105 win over the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic perfect from field, line for 11th triple-double of the season, Nuggets beat Grizzlies 142-105

events.name: Miami Heat at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro had 26 points and seven rebounds to help the short-handed Miami Heat beat the Golden State Warriors 114-102 on Thursday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyler Herro scores 26 points, short-handed Heat beat Warriors 114-102 for 4th straight win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 30 points, six rebounds, six assists and seven blocks and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Portland Trail Blazers 118-105 on Thursday night to snapped a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama scores 30 points, Spurs snap 5-game skid with a 118-105 win over Trail Blazers

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 17 points and 11 assists two days before his 39th birthday, Anthony Davis had 26 points and eight rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers sent the Charlotte Hornets to their ninth straight loss with a 133-112 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron closes in on 39th birthday with 17 points, 11 assists in Lakers' 133-112 win over Hornets
